{
  "title": [
    "triangle~"
  ],
  "description": "variable duty triangular wave",
  "origin": "cyclone",
  "categories": [
    "Signal Generators"
  ],
  "inlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "phase input signal"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    },
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "variable duty (peak position) from 1 to 0"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "outlets": [
    {
      "messages": [
        {
          "type": "signal",
          "description": "the triangle wavetable output based on args"
        }
      ],
      "repeat": false
    }
  ],
  "arguments": [
    {
      "type": "float",
      "description": "peak position from 1 to 0",
      "default": "0.5"
    }
  ],
  "flags": [
    {
      "name": "lo <float>",
      "description": "lowest point\ndefault: 1"
    },
    {
      "name": "hi <float>",
      "description": "highest point\ndefault: 1"
    }
  ],
  "methods": [
    {
      "type": "lo <float>",
      "description": "sets lowest point"
    },
    {
      "type": "hi <float>",
      "description": "sets highest point"
    }
  ],
  "body": "[triangle~] is a triangular wavetable that is read with phase values from 0 to 1 into the first inlet- a [phasor~] input turns it into a wavetable oscillator.\nA second inlet changes the position of the peak value (variable duty, from 0 to 1), going from sawtooth like waveforms to triangular ones.\nThe default lo/hi points are -1 and 1, but may be changed using the lo/hi messages to any given range."
}